Author: PartyTimeSexyDisco
Text: You can read the ingredients and see :) depends on the brand but I imagine lower cal ice cream will have eg skimmed or plant milk instead of full fat milk or cream, sweetener at least partly replacing sugar, and will probably have a more 'whipped' consistency (ie it has more air in it than regular ice cream - the same container would fit let's say 500 grams of regular but only 300 grams of diet). If it has a higher protein content than regular it will also be lower cal as the protein will likely be replacing fat, and 1 gram of protein has less cals than 1 gram of fat.
